1
00:00:04,139 --> 00:00:08,172
[ISUZU]
Amagi Transport says
they can add more buses.

2
00:00:08,272 --> 00:00:09,905
[ISUZU]
And as for the sports stadium...

3
00:00:10,005 --> 00:00:12,039
I haven't gotten
a definite response yet.

4
00:00:12,139 --> 00:00:14,472
[SEIYA]
Sounds good... Keep it up.

5
00:00:14,572 --> 00:00:18,072
[ISUZU]
I did get an answer from Moll
Mart about the‐

6
00:00:18,172 --> 00:00:19,205
...other thing.

7
00:00:19,305 --> 00:00:20,439
[ISUZU]
Kanie?

8
00:00:20,539 --> 00:00:23,972
[SEIYA]
Sorry... I feel kinda dizzy...

9
00:00:25,605 --> 00:00:28,805
[ISUZU]
(scared) Kanie! What's wrong?!

10
00:02:03,159 --> 00:02:04,792
[MUSE]
Mr. Kanie passed out?!

11
00:02:04,892 --> 00:02:06,259
[KOBORY]
What'd the doctor say?

12
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:08,292
[ISUZU]
Probably just exhaustion
mixed with a cold.

13
00:02:08,392 --> 00:02:10,559
[MUSE]
Good, that's not too serious.

14
00:02:10,659 --> 00:02:12,525
[KOBORY] We'd be in trouble if
he had to go to the hospital.
[SYLPHY] Nice poker face!

15
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:13,759
[SYLPHY] I'm stuck...

16
00:02:13,859 --> 00:02:15,392
[MUSE]
I wonder if we can help him.

17
00:02:15,492 --> 00:02:18,459
[MUSE]
I know! I could keep him
hydrated with my water spells!

18
00:02:18,559 --> 00:02:20,992
[SALAMA]
And I'll keep him warm with my
fire.

19
00:02:21,092 --> 00:02:23,259
[KOBORY]
And I'll bury him
to leech out the poison.

20
00:02:23,359 --> 00:02:24,659
[SALAMA] I don't think that'll
work for a cold...

21
00:02:24,759 --> 00:02:26,359
[SYLPHY] Whoa! I'm not worthy!

22
00:02:26,459 --> 00:02:28,825
[LATIFAH]
I'm sorry, I won't let you.

23
00:02:28,925 --> 00:02:31,659
[SEIYA]
But it's just a little cold.
The paperwork's piling up‐

24
00:02:31,759 --> 00:02:32,992
[LATIFAH]
Absolutely not‐

25
00:02:33,092 --> 00:02:34,325
I command you to remain at home

26
00:02:34,425 --> 00:02:36,292
until you've made a complete
recovery.

27
00:02:36,392 --> 00:02:39,425
[SEIYA]
Let me guess‐ you're not gonna
let me go to school either.

28
00:02:39,525 --> 00:02:41,192
[LATIFAH]
Sir Kanie.

29
00:02:41,292 --> 00:02:44,225
Do not underestimate
the importance of your health.

30
00:02:47,059 --> 00:02:49,025
[SEIYA]
(watching)

31
00:02:49,125 --> 00:02:50,525
I hope you feel better soon...

32
00:02:50,625 --> 00:02:52,625
Now get some rest.

33
00:02:59,159 --> 00:03:00,692
[SEIYA]
Well that's great...

34
00:03:04,559 --> 00:03:07,492
[ISUZU]
How are you feeling, Kanie?

35
00:03:07,592 --> 00:03:09,259
[SEIYA]
Hey Sento.

36
00:03:09,359 --> 00:03:11,825
[SEIYA]
Look, could you please tell
that princess of yours

37
00:03:11,925 --> 00:03:13,125
not to worry so much?

38
00:03:14,525 --> 00:03:17,959
[SEIYA]
Hold on... What's that
weird thing on your head?

39
00:03:18,059 --> 00:03:20,459
[ISUZU]
Just ignore it.

40
00:03:20,559 --> 00:03:22,392
[SEIYA]
I've missed a lot of
school days already.

41
00:03:22,492 --> 00:03:24,559
I can't afford to take
any more ti‐

42
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:26,825
[SEIYA]
S‐Sento?!

43
00:03:26,925 --> 00:03:28,825
[SEIYA]
Hey! (nervous)

44
00:03:28,925 --> 00:03:31,825
[ISUZU]
I want to be more than
just your secretary‐ Kanie...

45
00:03:31,925 --> 00:03:34,659
[SEIYA]
Whoa, I think this summer heat's
getting to your head!

46
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:36,292
[ISUZU] Don't pull away.
[SEIYA] (extended awkwardness)

47
00:03:36,392 --> 00:03:39,392
[ISUZU]
I need to tell you...
I... I want you...

48
00:03:41,225 --> 00:03:43,859
[TIRAMY]
Just kidding‐ it was me
all along mii!

49
00:03:43,959 --> 00:03:44,859
[MACARON]
You sucker‐ron!

50
00:03:44,959 --> 00:03:45,859
[SEIYA]
What the...?

51
00:03:45,959 --> 00:03:47,125
[TIRAMY]
(chortling)

52
00:03:47,225 --> 00:03:48,859
[SEIYA]
How did you...

53
00:03:48,959 --> 00:03:50,259
[TIRAMY/MACARON]
(explode into laughter)

54
00:03:50,359 --> 00:03:52,425
[TIRAMY]
It's a magic Isuzu costume!

55
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:58,025
[MACARON]
Yeah, we modified it from
the ones they use in the
Diggery Clan‐ron!

56
00:03:58,125 --> 00:03:59,459
[SEIYA]
That's messed up.

57
00:03:59,559 --> 00:04:00,992
[TIRAMY]
Well at least now you don't have
to worry

58
00:04:01,092 --> 00:04:02,259
about missing your classes‐mii!

59
00:04:02,359 --> 00:04:04,359
[SEIYA]
I can't believe what
I'm hearing.

60
00:04:04,459 --> 00:04:06,325
You guys want to make
a costume of me and go to my‐

61
00:04:06,425 --> 00:04:09,059
[MACARON]
Mhm! That's right‐ we wanna go
to school in your place!

62
00:04:09,159 --> 00:04:10,759
[TIRAMY]
It's a pretty complete
prototype.

63
00:04:10,859 --> 00:04:13,325
Unfortunately‐ we weren't
able to get an exact reference

64
00:04:13,425 --> 00:04:14,792
for the parts underneath
the clothes...

65
00:04:14,892 --> 00:04:17,392
so we used our
imaginations‐mii!

66
00:04:19,059 --> 00:04:20,359
[MACARON/TIRAMY]
(realize)

67
00:04:20,459 --> 00:04:22,859
[TIRAMY]
Oh... when'd you get here Isuzu?

68
00:04:22,959 --> 00:04:25,725
[MACARON/TIRAMY]
(trembling)

69
00:04:27,325 --> 00:04:29,693
[MOFFLE]
Moff... I don't think
it's a bad idea.

70
00:04:29,793 --> 00:04:31,593
I mean‐ what else
are you gonna do?

71
00:04:31,693 --> 00:04:34,259
It's not like you have
any friends.
[SEIYA] (offended)

72
00:04:34,359 --> 00:04:36,259
[MOFFLE]
It'll be fine
if they keep quiet.

73
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:37,293
[SEIYA]
(annoyed) (stunned) Ugh...

74
00:04:37,393 --> 00:04:38,593
[ISUZU]
Then it's settled.

75
00:04:40,093 --> 00:04:44,059
[GIRL]
Oh, I know. What about
spaghetti?

76
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:45,893
[ISUZU]
What an amazing item...

77
00:04:45,993 --> 00:04:47,993
It's exactly like the original.

78
00:04:48,093 --> 00:04:48,793
(incoming stampede)

79
00:04:48,893 --> 00:04:50,026
[SEIYA]
(gasp)

80
00:04:50,126 --> 00:04:53,026
[BRAT A/BRAT B/BRAT C]
Wahoo! Heh heh!

81
00:04:53,126 --> 00:04:54,393
[BRAT A]
Jackpot!

82
00:04:54,493 --> 00:04:55,293
I smell a girl!

83
00:04:55,393 --> 00:04:56,426
[BRAT A/BRAT B/BRAT C]
(menacing)

84
00:04:56,526 --> 00:04:57,593
[BRAT A/BRAT B/BRAT C]
(MENACING)

85
00:04:57,693 --> 00:04:58,759
[SEIYA]
(gulp)

86
00:04:58,859 --> 00:04:59,893
[BRAT C]
False alarm.

87
00:04:59,993 --> 00:05:02,093
[BRAT A/BRAT B/BRAT C]
(cackling)

88
00:05:02,193 --> 00:05:03,026
[SEIYA]
(relieved)

89
00:05:03,126 --> 00:05:04,059
[SHIINA]
K... Kanie?

90
00:05:04,159 --> 00:05:05,093
[SEIYA]
(startled)

91
00:05:05,193 --> 00:05:06,593
[SHIINA]
Good morning, sir!

92
00:05:06,693 --> 00:05:08,893
I heard you passed out from a
cold recently and um...

93
00:05:08,993 --> 00:05:10,293
Wait. what's that?

94
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:11,559
[SEIYA] (like Isuzu) G‐good
morning, Miss Chujo...

95
00:05:11,659 --> 00:05:12,359
It's nothing.

96
00:05:12,459 --> 00:05:13,326
[SHIINA]
What?

97
00:05:13,426 --> 00:05:15,893
Ah, I mean,
good morning, Chujo...

98
00:05:15,993 --> 00:05:17,559
And yeah, I'm not sick anymore.

99
00:05:17,659 --> 00:05:18,826
Oh...

100
00:05:18,926 --> 00:05:21,093
Anyway do I look nice
and handsome today?

101
00:05:21,193 --> 00:05:23,359
[SHIINA]
I'm not sure how to respond
to that...

102
00:05:23,459 --> 00:05:25,393
But you seem like you're in a
good mood!

103
00:05:25,493 --> 00:05:26,726
[SEIYA] You think so?
[SHIINA] Yeah...

104
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:27,826
I mean, most of the time

105
00:05:27,926 --> 00:05:29,359
you just kind of ignore me.

106
00:05:29,459 --> 00:05:34,093
[SHIINA]
So I... I'm uh... I'm happy, I
guess!(turn away)

107
00:05:35,326 --> 00:05:36,526
[ISUZU]
Goodness...

108
00:05:36,626 --> 00:05:39,559
Kanie must really
treat that girl poorly.

109
00:05:42,759 --> 00:05:44,259
[SEIYA]
Hm?

110
00:05:50,826 --> 00:05:53,159
(reading)
"I've liked you ever
since my first year.

111
00:05:53,259 --> 00:05:55,059
No matter what people
say about you,

112
00:05:55,159 --> 00:05:57,193
I can tell you're
a really nice person.

113
00:05:57,293 --> 00:05:58,926
If it isn't too much trouble,

114
00:05:59,026 --> 00:06:00,993
I'd like you to meet me
behind the gymnasium

115
00:06:01,093 --> 00:06:02,393
after school this afternoon.

116
00:06:02,493 --> 00:06:05,559
Please give me the chance to
tell you how I feel"?!

117
00:06:06,826 --> 00:06:09,193
[TEACHER]
(drones on lesson under)

118
00:06:09,293 --> 00:06:10,759
[ISUZU]
What should I do?

119
00:06:10,859 --> 00:06:13,526
I thought of texting Kanie
to see what he thinks about it,

120
00:06:13,626 --> 00:06:18,093
but he's still resting
and I'd hate to bother him.

121
00:06:18,193 --> 00:06:20,693
[TEACHER]
This concept is sure to be on
your test.

122
00:06:21,859 --> 00:06:23,126
[SEIYA]
It was a mistake?

123
00:06:23,226 --> 00:06:24,993
[KANAE]
Yeah, I could've sworn that
shoebox

124
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:28,026
belonged to Kimura
from class 2‐5.

125
00:06:28,126 --> 00:06:31,959
So I never meant for that love
letter to go to you.

126
00:06:32,059 --> 00:06:33,859
Um... what's that on your head?

127
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:34,893
[SEIYA]
Just ignore it.

128
00:06:34,993 --> 00:06:35,959
Uh, so what you're saying is

129
00:06:36,059 --> 00:06:37,359
you're not in love with Kanie...

130
00:06:37,459 --> 00:06:39,593
I mean, so I'm not the guy
you're in love with huh?

131
00:06:39,693 --> 00:06:44,259
[KANAE]
No... I guess you're upset...
I really am sorry about this!

132
00:06:44,359 --> 00:06:46,259
[SEIYA] It's quite alright.
[KANAE] Huh?

133
00:06:46,359 --> 00:06:47,926
[SEIYA]
Everyone makes mistakes
sometimes.

134
00:06:48,026 --> 00:06:48,959
You didn't sign the letter,

135
00:06:49,059 --> 00:06:50,026
so you could've just run away

136
00:06:50,126 --> 00:06:51,293
when you realized what happened,

137
00:06:51,393 --> 00:06:52,426
but you went out of your way

138
00:06:52,526 --> 00:06:53,893
to apologize and
set things right.

139
00:06:53,993 --> 00:06:55,393
That was very professional.

140
00:06:55,493 --> 00:06:56,959
[KANAE]
Does that mean you forgive me?

141
00:06:57,059 --> 00:06:58,959
There's nothing to forgive
you for...

142
00:06:59,059 --> 00:07:00,393
Thanks for being considerate.

143
00:07:00,493 --> 00:07:02,726
[KANAE]
(happy) Wow, thank you so much,
Kanie.

144
00:07:02,826 --> 00:07:04,359
When I realized what I had done,

145
00:07:04,459 --> 00:07:06,693
I was so afraid you were going
to yell at me or something.

146
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:08,359
[SEIYA]
It's fine... In fact...

147
00:07:08,459 --> 00:07:10,926
I wish you the best in all your
endeavors, Miss Kanae Tsuchida.

148
00:07:11,026 --> 00:07:14,926
[KANAE]
You know... I'm kind of happy
I misplaced that letter.

149
00:07:15,026 --> 00:07:15,859
[SEIYA]
(confused)

150
00:07:15,959 --> 00:07:17,393
Well, goodbye for now!

151
00:07:19,226 --> 00:07:21,693
[SEIYA]
"For now"?

152
00:07:21,793 --> 00:07:23,693
[MACARON]
So you didn't have any
major issues?

153
00:07:23,793 --> 00:07:26,193
[ISUZU]
No, there was nothing worth
reporting...

154
00:07:26,293 --> 00:07:28,126
I hope you'll be as
successful tomorrow.

155
00:07:28,226 --> 00:07:31,126
[MACARON]
Ah high school...
so many memories‐ron!

156
00:07:31,226 --> 00:07:35,059
I don't suppose you've ever
heard of Dokidoki Melody High
School in Maple Land?

157
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:37,426
It's super‐famous for being full
of troublemakers‐ron.

158
00:07:37,526 --> 00:07:39,959
[ISUZU]
Yes, I'm always hearing about
violent incidents.

159
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:44,659
[MACARON]
I was top sheep back in the day.
Got expelled halfway through,
though.

160
00:07:44,759 --> 00:07:47,593
We had a little scrap with some
guys from another school
so they gave me the boot‐

161
00:07:47,693 --> 00:07:49,626
[ISUZU] I'm not interested.
[MACARON] Oh. Well.

162
00:07:49,726 --> 00:07:51,893
[ISUZU]
Just try not to cause any
problems.

163
00:07:51,993 --> 00:07:53,259
[MACARON]
Don't worry about me.

164
00:07:53,359 --> 00:07:55,626
I can blend right in
with those youngsters‐ron.

165
00:07:57,126 --> 00:07:59,059
[SEIYA]
(relaxing)

166
00:07:59,859 --> 00:08:02,226
[TEACHER]
Ah... Listen, son...

167
00:08:02,326 --> 00:08:05,893
You can't do that in class...
and what's that on your head?

168
00:08:05,993 --> 00:08:08,926
[SEIYA]
Just ignore it and focus on
doing your job, old man.

169
00:08:09,026 --> 00:08:10,693
[TEACHER]
Wh... what did you say?!

170
00:08:10,793 --> 00:08:12,693
[SEIYA]
You're such a drag‐ron!

171
00:08:12,793 --> 00:08:13,459
[TEACHER]
(startled)

172
00:08:13,559 --> 00:08:15,059
S‐stay back!

173
00:08:15,159 --> 00:08:16,426
I don't want to fi‐(speechless)

174
00:08:16,526 --> 00:08:18,793
[SEIYA]
Hey teach...
I'm not feelin' so good,

175
00:08:18,893 --> 00:08:20,693
so I'm gonna go see
the nurse now.

176
00:08:21,326 --> 00:08:21,826
See ya.

177
00:08:21,926 --> 00:08:23,026
[TEACHER]
Huh?

178
00:08:27,893 --> 00:08:30,226
[SHIINA]
Um, is that you, Mr. Kanie?

179
00:08:30,326 --> 00:08:33,226
[SEIYA]
Hm? Oh... it's you‐ron.

180
00:08:33,326 --> 00:08:35,126
[SHIINA]
You‐ron? I don't‐

181
00:08:35,226 --> 00:08:37,659
[SEIYA]
I forgot you were my
classmate‐ron.

182
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:38,793
[SHIINA]
What?

183
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,293
[SEIYA]
Lunchtime already, huh?

184
00:08:40,393 --> 00:08:41,693
Man, this place is so boring

185
00:08:41,793 --> 00:08:43,159
I can't even smoke a cigarette.

186
00:08:43,259 --> 00:08:45,259
I don't know how much I can take
before I snap.

187
00:08:45,359 --> 00:08:46,493
[SHIINA]
Did you say "snap"?

188
00:08:46,593 --> 00:08:48,426
[SEIYA]
Hey, wanna skip class with me?

189
00:08:48,526 --> 00:08:50,626
I'm gonna go play some
pachinko later.

190
00:08:50,726 --> 00:08:51,659
[SHIINA]
(shock)

191
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:54,726
N‐no thanks, I'm good, bye!

192
00:08:54,826 --> 00:08:57,126
Jeez, was it something I said?

193
00:08:57,226 --> 00:08:59,259
[KIMURA]
What do you mean, mistake?

194
00:08:59,359 --> 00:09:01,693
[KIMURA]
Terano told me you were planning
to give me a letter...

195
00:09:01,793 --> 00:09:03,193
What happened to that?

196
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:04,526
[KANAE]
I was going to...

197
00:09:04,626 --> 00:09:06,593
but now I can't figure out
my true feelings.

198
00:09:06,693 --> 00:09:09,793
[KANAE]
I'm having trouble deciding if
that's what I really want to do.

199
00:09:09,893 --> 00:09:11,226
[KIMURA]
But how can you say that?!

200
00:09:11,326 --> 00:09:12,393
If you had asked me out,

201
00:09:12,493 --> 00:09:14,326
I would've said yes in a
heartbeat!

202
00:09:14,426 --> 00:09:17,359
[KANAE]
I know, but things have
changed...

203
00:09:17,459 --> 00:09:20,193
[MACARON]
They could use some love advice
from yours truly‐ron.

204
00:09:20,293 --> 00:09:21,826
[SEIYA]
Take it easy there, son.

205
00:09:21,926 --> 00:09:22,693
[KANAE/KIMURA]
(surprised)

206
00:09:22,793 --> 00:09:23,959
[KANAE]
Kanie?!

207
00:09:24,059 --> 00:09:25,459
[KIMURA]
Were you spying on us?!

208
00:09:25,559 --> 00:09:27,526
[SEIYA]
Oh, don't have a cow, ron.

209
00:09:27,626 --> 00:09:28,593
[KIMURA]
"Ron"?

210
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:30,059
[SEIYA]
I mean, uh...(ahem)

211
00:09:30,159 --> 00:09:31,593
Take it from me kid,

212
00:09:31,693 --> 00:09:34,026
the harder you chase after
a lady the faster she runs away.

213
00:09:34,126 --> 00:09:36,393
You just gotta be cool...
Better to step aside

214
00:09:36,493 --> 00:09:37,993
and let her collect her
thoughts for a while

215
00:09:38,093 --> 00:09:40,026
than make an ass of
yourself‐ron... Understand?

216
00:09:40,126 --> 00:09:42,193
[KIMURA]
Who asked you?!
And what's that?!

217
00:09:42,293 --> 00:09:43,359
[SEIYA]
Just ignore it.

218
00:09:43,459 --> 00:09:44,993
[KIMURA]
I don't need advice from

219
00:09:45,093 --> 00:09:46,826
the guy who got Tsuchida's
love letter by mistake!

220
00:09:46,926 --> 00:09:48,293
[SEIYA]
Huh?!

221
00:09:48,393 --> 00:09:50,659
[KIMURA]
She had her eye on me
in the first place,

222
00:09:50,759 --> 00:09:52,126
and then THIS had
to happen!

223
00:09:52,226 --> 00:09:54,793
You're the last person
I want to talk to about this,

224
00:09:54,893 --> 00:09:55,726
you got that?!

225
00:09:55,826 --> 00:09:56,859
[SEIYA]
Wait a sec...

