452
00:17:50,795 --> 00:17:51,828
and your bullshit!

453
00:17:51,928 --> 00:17:53,228
[TERANO/SASAKI/YAMAMOTO]
(stunned)

454
00:17:53,328 --> 00:17:55,028
Running your mouths
about love and sincerity...

455
00:17:55,128 --> 00:17:57,795
You can't just throw those words
around like they're nothing!

456
00:17:57,895 --> 00:17:59,328
You're a bunch of kids!

457
00:17:59,428 --> 00:18:00,828
Don't make me laugh.

458
00:18:00,928 --> 00:18:02,895
you three don't know the first
moffin' thing about love!

459
00:18:02,995 --> 00:18:04,761
[ISUZU]
Please don't get upset,
Lord Moffle.

460
00:18:04,861 --> 00:18:06,428
[SEIYA]
You date some boy
you barely know,

461
00:18:06,528 --> 00:18:07,795
you think you're in love,

462
00:18:07,895 --> 00:18:10,328
then you complain about
heartbreak afterwards?!

463
00:18:10,428 --> 00:18:12,061
You think life's that easy?!

464
00:18:12,161 --> 00:18:13,628
[SEIYA]
What, does it make you feel cool

465
00:18:13,728 --> 00:18:15,895
to pretend to be angry for
your friend's sake,

466
00:18:15,995 --> 00:18:16,528
is that it?

467
00:18:16,628 --> 00:18:17,595
You're full of it!

468
00:18:17,695 --> 00:18:18,695
[TERANO/YAMAMOTO/SASAKI]
(gasp)

469
00:18:21,628 --> 00:18:23,428
[TERANO]
(stunned)Whoa!

470
00:18:23,528 --> 00:18:24,695
[SEIYA]
When the pain is bad enough

471
00:18:24,795 --> 00:18:26,161
to make you wish
you were dead...

472
00:18:26,261 --> 00:18:28,995
THAT... THAT'S what love is!

473
00:18:29,095 --> 00:18:30,828
Wait 'til the woman you've
loved for over ten years

474
00:18:30,928 --> 00:18:32,695
gets married to some
bastard you hate!

475
00:18:32,795 --> 00:18:35,661
You can't even imagine the agony
I felt that day!

476
00:18:35,761 --> 00:18:37,128
[SEIYA]
And then ten years later,

477
00:18:37,228 --> 00:18:39,328
she comes and asks me to take
care of her daughter?

478
00:18:39,428 --> 00:18:40,861
Do you know how that feels?!

479
00:18:40,961 --> 00:18:42,861
[ISUZU] (surprised)
[SEIYA] No! Because you're
children!

480
00:18:42,961 --> 00:18:44,295
[ISUZU]
Wait a minute sir.

481
00:18:44,395 --> 00:18:46,161
Is this in reference to
Princess Latifah's mother?

482
00:18:46,261 --> 00:18:48,528
[SEIYA]
Shut the moff up,
it's hypothetical!

483
00:18:48,628 --> 00:18:49,861
[TERANO]
What's his problem?!

484
00:18:49,961 --> 00:18:51,795
[SASAKI]
Yeah. he's really creeping
me out.

485
00:18:51,895 --> 00:18:53,461
[YAMAMOTO]
And what does "moff" mean?

486
00:18:53,561 --> 00:18:54,661
[KIMURA]
Stop it, guys!

487
00:18:54,761 --> 00:18:55,961
[SASAKI/YAMAMOTO/TERANO]
(surprised)

488
00:18:56,728 --> 00:18:57,561
[KANAE]
Kimura!

489
00:18:57,661 --> 00:18:59,061
[KIMURA]
I'm sorry...

490
00:18:59,161 --> 00:19:01,628
The only reason Kanie acted
like that was for my sake!

491
00:19:01,728 --> 00:19:03,028
[ALL]
Huh?!

492
00:19:03,128 --> 00:19:04,495
[KIMURA]
He said all those crazy things

493
00:19:04,595 --> 00:19:05,695
and acted like a scumbag
on purpose

494
00:19:05,795 --> 00:19:07,728
to make Tsuchida hate his guts!

495
00:19:07,828 --> 00:19:11,095
That way maybe she'd
want to be with me instead!

496
00:19:11,195 --> 00:19:12,295
[KIMURA]
Right, Kanie?

497
00:19:12,395 --> 00:19:14,395
[SEIYA]
I what...? Uhhh, yeah...

498
00:19:14,495 --> 00:19:15,861
[KIMURA]
When I asked Kanie for advice

499
00:19:15,961 --> 00:19:17,961
about how to patch everything up
with Tsuchida...

500
00:19:18,061 --> 00:19:20,928
he had a plan...
He said the only way to get
things back to normal

501
00:19:21,028 --> 00:19:22,961
was to make her not
like him anymore.

502
00:19:23,061 --> 00:19:25,928
I know this mess ended up making
me look bad too...

503
00:19:26,028 --> 00:19:28,895
But I swear I'll try really hard
to be the best guy for you.

504
00:19:28,995 --> 00:19:31,095
[KIMURA]
So do you think maybe
you could give me a chance?

505
00:19:31,195 --> 00:19:34,361
[KANAE]
O‐okay... If you're sure that's
what you want too.

506
00:19:34,461 --> 00:19:35,695
[TERANO]
Well then if the two of you

507
00:19:35,795 --> 00:19:37,395
don't have anything left to be
upset over...

508
00:19:37,495 --> 00:19:39,328
I guess I have nothing to say.

509
00:19:39,428 --> 00:19:40,361
[KIMURA]
Awesome!...

510
00:19:40,461 --> 00:19:41,828
Thank you for understanding!

511
00:19:41,928 --> 00:19:46,961
[KIMURA]
It's nice to have friends,
huh?(big laughter)

512
00:19:49,261 --> 00:19:52,328
[SEIYA] (unzipping)
Thanks for the
heads‐up, Chujo...

513
00:19:52,428 --> 00:19:53,995
It all worked out,
thanks to you.

514
00:19:54,095 --> 00:19:57,061
[SHIINA]
Sure... I knew something weird
must be going on...

515
00:19:57,161 --> 00:20:00,728
It's a good thing I was able to
get in contact with you.

516
00:20:00,828 --> 00:20:02,061
[SEIYA]
I appreciate it.

517
00:20:02,161 --> 00:20:03,961
[SEIYA]
Hopefully I can figure out a way

518
00:20:04,061 --> 00:20:05,995
to explain all this
to Kimura later.

519
00:20:06,095 --> 00:20:09,161
[SHIINA]
I'm surprised you didn't get mad
at Mr. Moffle and the other two.

520
00:20:09,261 --> 00:20:11,795
You almost made a lot of enemies
because of this mess.

521
00:20:11,895 --> 00:20:13,761
[SEIYA]
Nah... I'm not mad...

522
00:20:13,861 --> 00:20:15,395
Either way, those idiots only
did it

523
00:20:15,495 --> 00:20:16,961
because they wanted to
help me out.

524
00:20:17,061 --> 00:20:19,428
[SEIYA]
How could I be mad at that?

525
00:20:19,528 --> 00:20:20,261
[SHIINA]
(smile)

526
00:20:20,361 --> 00:20:21,261
[SEIYA]
What?

527
00:20:21,361 --> 00:20:22,161
[SHIINA]
Oh it's nothing.

528
00:20:22,261 --> 00:20:23,528
I was just thinking

529
00:20:23,628 --> 00:20:25,595
how you reacted the way
I expected you would.

530
00:20:25,695 --> 00:20:26,495
[SEIYA]
Huh?

531
00:20:26,595 --> 00:20:28,095
It's no big deal...

532
00:20:28,195 --> 00:20:29,295
I gotta go!

533
00:20:36,395 --> 00:20:37,228
[SEIYA]
Sento. you made it.

534
00:20:37,328 --> 00:20:38,595
[LATIFAH]
(happy)

535
00:20:38,695 --> 00:20:40,495
It's good to see that you're
back on the job...

536
00:20:40,595 --> 00:20:42,895
I take it you've fully
recovered then.

537
00:20:42,995 --> 00:20:44,661
[LATIFAH]
Look at this, Lady Isuzu...

538
00:20:44,761 --> 00:20:46,928
Sir Kanie is very
peculiar!(giggle)

539
00:20:47,028 --> 00:20:48,461
[ISUZU]
Did something happen?

540
00:20:48,561 --> 00:20:49,928
[LATIFAH]
Just look at the way

541
00:20:50,028 --> 00:20:51,861
he tries his best to preserve
the strawberry on top

542
00:20:51,961 --> 00:20:53,428
until the last possible moment!

543
00:20:53,528 --> 00:20:55,761
[SEIYA]
(surprised)What? is that weird?

544
00:20:55,861 --> 00:20:58,928
You appear to be healthy enough
to return to school tomorrow.

545
00:20:59,028 --> 00:21:00,928
Oh yeah. I'm perfectly fine
now...

546
00:21:01,028 --> 00:21:02,928
Sorry for the trouble. Sento.

547
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:06,395
[ISUZU]
No... I probably wasn't of very
much help to you in the end.

548
00:21:06,495 --> 00:21:09,695
In fact, I may have caused YOU
trouble.

549
00:21:09,795 --> 00:21:13,061
Well, you can fill me in
later... Are you hungry?

550
00:21:13,161 --> 00:21:15,261
[LATIFAH]
Yes, we have croquettes!

551
00:21:15,361 --> 00:21:16,628
[ISUZU]
Thank you.

552
00:21:16,728 --> 00:21:17,895
[LATIFAH]
Speaking of which,

553
00:21:17,995 --> 00:21:19,695
I've thought of a
new croquette recipe!

554
00:21:19,795 --> 00:21:21,595
[LATIFAH]
If I add sugar to the batter...

555
00:21:21,695 --> 00:21:22,995
they'll be even more appealing

556
00:21:23,095 --> 00:21:25,261
to visitors with a sweet tooth
won't they?

557
00:21:25,361 --> 00:21:27,561
[SEIYA]
Sounds good... I think the
Maple Kitchen

558
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:28,995
could benefit from
a new menu item.

559
00:21:29,095 --> 00:21:30,695
[LATIFAH]
Then would it be alright if you

560
00:21:30,795 --> 00:21:32,661
sampled the new recipe to make
sure it's perfect

561
00:21:32,761 --> 00:21:34,161
before we serve it to the
guests?

562
00:21:34,261 --> 00:21:36,628
[SEIYA]
Oh I get it.
So I'm a guinea pig now.

563
00:21:36,728 --> 00:21:38,561
[LATIFAH] Oh no...!
I didn't mean it that way!

564
00:21:38,661 --> 00:21:40,461
[SEIYA]
(laugh) It's fine.

565
00:21:40,561 --> 00:21:43,528
[LATIFAH]
Then I'll go ahead and make a
few first thing in the morning.

566
00:21:43,628 --> 00:21:44,595
[SEIYA]
Can't wait to try 'em.

567
00:21:44,695 --> 00:21:45,695
[LATIFAH]
Perfect!

568
00:21:45,795 --> 00:21:47,695
I'm sure you'll like them.

569
00:22:10,262 --> 00:22:11,195
[MUSE]
(determined)

570
00:22:11,295 --> 00:22:14,629
[MUSE]
(exert) Haaa! Agghh!

571
00:22:14,729 --> 00:22:19,895
[MUSE]
It's not good enough!

572
00:23:51,629 --> 00:23:54,595
[ISUZU/SEIYA]
Time for the
attractions spotlight.

573
00:23:54,695 --> 00:23:56,729
[ISUZU]
Today's feature is Save the
Earth.

574
00:23:56,829 --> 00:23:59,795
It's a fun‐filled presentation
about Earth science.

575
00:23:59,895 --> 00:24:02,062
[SEIYA]
Oh okay, so it's like a
documentary type thing?

576
00:24:02,162 --> 00:24:05,529
[ISUZU]
Sort of. The audience
experiences a lengthy lecture

577
00:24:05,629 --> 00:24:06,429
from Future the globe

578
00:24:06,529 --> 00:24:07,762
about the many ways

579
00:24:07,862 --> 00:24:09,962
in which humanity destroys
our precious planet.

580
00:24:10,062 --> 00:24:12,262
[SEIYA]
That doesn't sound fun at all.

581
00:24:12,362 --> 00:24:13,695
[ISUZU]
And then after the show,

582
00:24:13,795 --> 00:24:15,829
he demands a 2,000 yen donation
from each visitor.

583
00:24:15,929 --> 00:24:18,129
[SEIYA]
We should shut that down!

